Title: 1984
A dystopian story about a totalitarian society controlled by surveillance, propaganda, and thought police. Winston Smith secretly rebels in search of truth and freedom. Themes: totalitarianism, freedom, truth.

Title: The Hobbit
Bilbo Baggins, a comfort-loving hobbit, is drawn into an epic quest with dwarves to reclaim a treasure guarded by the dragon Smaug. Along the way, he discovers courage, friendship, and the thrill of adventure. Themes: friendship, adventure, courage.

Title: Pride and Prejudice
Elizabeth Bennet navigates societal expectations, family drama, and her evolving feelings for the enigmatic Mr. Darcy. Themes: love, social class, prejudice.

Title: To Kill a Mockingbird
Scout Finch recalls her childhood in the racially divided South, focusing on her father Atticus Finch’s defense of a Black man wrongly accused of a crime. Themes: justice, racism, moral growth.

Title: The Great Gatsby
Nick Carraway observes the life of the mysterious millionaire Jay Gatsby, whose obsession with Daisy Buchanan leads to tragedy. Themes: the American Dream, love, illusion.

Title: Harry Potter and the Sorcerer’s Stone
An orphaned boy discovers he’s a wizard and attends Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry, where he makes friends, faces dangers, and uncovers his past. Themes: friendship, courage, magic.

Title: The Catcher in the Rye
Holden Caulfield recounts a few days in his life after being expelled from school, reflecting on alienation, innocence, and growing up. Themes: isolation, adolescence, identity.

Title: The Alchemist
Santiago, a shepherd, follows his dream to find treasure in Egypt. Along the way, he learns about love, destiny, and the importance of pursuing one’s personal legend. Themes: self-discovery, destiny, perseverance.

Title: Fahrenheit 451
In a future where books are banned, fireman Guy Montag begins to question the society that burns them and seeks knowledge and freedom. Themes: censorship, knowledge, freedom.

Title: Moby-Dick
Captain Ahab obsessively hunts the great white whale, Moby Dick, leading his crew on a dangerous journey. Themes: obsession, revenge, fate.

Title: Jane Eyre
An orphaned governess falls in love with her employer, Mr. Rochester, but discovers a dark secret. Themes: love, independence, morality.

